The trailing values are how one indicates to FRESCO that we are copying the same target partition info and which OMPs to use. 

1 | COPYt | copy target state/pair #1, i.e. keep 58Ni as 0+ g.s.
1 | KP    | use optical potential set 1 / same entrance-channel potential bookkeeping


The rest of these Card 7's are for discretizating the continuum.
These are all MIDPOINT energies of each bin of width defined in the form factors.
In Partition 1 Card 7 we are manually building the continuum into energy "bins" of energy "widths" of our choosing. 

