  Normal form factor definition for 6Li ground state
  1    1 2 1 0   2 0   1.0   1.0    3  0  1.4737  1  1  0 		        | 6Li GS

  ------------------------------------------------------------------- |

  2    1 2 1 0   1 2   1.0   3.0    7  0 -0.4950 14  3  0-90 -0.9700	|

  Form factors for the continuum begin here after the binding energy S_a(6Li) - Ex
  I'll explicitly label every input for form factor #2, but continuum-related inputs start from KBPOT onward:

  2           | KN1   | form-factor index
  blank/0     | KN2   | no range; this is just FF #2
  1           | IC1   | partition containing core/composite nucleus
  2           | IC2   | other partition involved in the form factor
  1           | IN    | particle is in projectile side
  0           | KIND  | ordinary one-particle (LN,SN)JN form factor

  blank       | CH1   | no special cluster label
  1           | NN    | number of radial nodes
  2           | L     | orbital angular momentum l = 2
  blank/0     | LMAX  | unused for KIND = 0
  1.0         | SN    | intrinsic spin of transferred/bound particle; here deuteron spin s = 1
  blank/0     | IA    | core state index; omitted/default
  3.0         | JN    | total single-particle angular momentum j = 3
  blank/0     | IB    | composite state index; omitted/default

  7           | KBPOT | binding potential index
  0           | KRPOT | transfer potential index
  -0.4950     | BE    | continuum bin midpoint energy
  14          | ISC   | continuum weighting prescription
  3           | IPC   | print control
  0           | NFL   | wavefuntion file unit
  -90         | NAM   | use 90 integration steps in continuum-bin averaging
  -0.9700     | AMPL  | UPPER bin spacing

  So physically FF #2 is roughly:
      α+d,ℓ=2,s=1,j=3+,Ebin​≈0.495 MeV
  using POT = 7 defined above.

