   ***** Transfer overlaps *****
   
  3   1   7 0-2 5
   
   3       | ICTO   | couple TO partition 3
   1       | ICFROM | couple FROM partition 1
 
   7       | KIND   | finite-range transfer coupling
 
   0       | IP1    | POST form transfer operator (IP1 = 1 for PRIOR form)
   -2      | IP2    | non-orthogonality remnant treatment
   5       | IP3    | remnant/core-core potential index

  KIND 7 --> finite-range = CRC alpha-transfer coupling!
  This card says: “Perform finite-range transfer coupling between partitions 1 and 3.”
  i.e. this means
    6Li+58Ni ↔ d+62Zn
  via α-transfer (the actual CRC reaction step).

  IP3 = 5 
  from the manual: IP3 = KPCORE. This means "which potential to use between the two cores in the remnant interaction.
  So if IP3=5, then it uses potential set 5 in the remnant/core-core interaction.
  5 = alpha + 58Ni optical potential --> MAKES PERFECT PHYSICAL SENSE!!!

